The paper focuses on the application of reinforcement learning in robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning and neural networks in learning policies suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The incorporation of perceptual representation using deep learning also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the mention of dynamic control systems suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY).
